19:
Hmm, but everything that happened
was just a dream, right?
23: That doesn't mean it wasn't real!
28:
Indeed. It's undeniable that Couette
has the power to affect reality
through her dreams.
33: I was there. She isn't lying.
38:
But that tin can isn't speaking or
moving. How do we know you're
telling the whole truth?
58:
If you ask me, it's more fun to take a
leap of faith than doubt everything
you hear.
61:
Besides, I think I've got some proof

morning. Do you know what it is?
71: Huh... Isn't that a Curse Crystal?
75:
A what now? You recognize that

79:
Learned about it when Adjudicus
helped me out the other day. I don't
know why it's such a surprise
though. You should've seen one
before.
84:
Ah... It's a type of crystal from
Pandemonium, correct?
88:
Yeah. They react to thoughts and
restructure themselves, recording a
person's memories inside.
92:
A mineral that contains memories...
Hehehe, the whole concept is a little
romantic, don't you think?
96:
If we're searching for treasure, I'd be
happy to join. I'm sure Rei will wilt
with envy once I tell her all about
how I joined the Crimson Blades on
an adventure.
100:

different places you visited in your
dream?

Awesome! Sounds to me like it's

125:
Judging by Rooma's reaction, it
must be nearby!
133:
With Rooma knowing where all the
treasure is, we'll gather everything in

137:
So don't worry too much. Your little
buddy will be chatting with you in no
time.
156:
Heh... Heheh... I'm going to keel over...
It's so hot...
160:

those fancy layers...
164:
Excuse you! This outfit was a special
gift from everyone at the academy!
168:
Besides, a magnificent witch should
always be dressed to impress, no
matter where or when!
171:
Is it still impressive when you're
dripping with sweat? Your makeup's
gonna melt off.
185:
Hehehe, you're such a sweet child,
Couette. Unlike a certain lout over
there.
188:
Never lose that kindness of yours, or
else you'll grow up to be like him!
204:
I've caused you and the others so
much trouble... If only I was more

208: This is no trouble at all, dear.
211:

there's such a thing as being TOO
considerate.
215:
You should learn from my example.
While I'm not proud of the fact, I'm
an expert in relying on others!
220:
You're not proud, but you're still
gonna boast about it, huh...
224:
The point isâ€”you should be more
selfish. Otherwise you'll never
become a capable adult.
233:
Hmm, I dunno about that last part,
but I do agree that you should be
more in tune with your own wants.
235:
Besides, everyone's enjoying
themselves with the treasure hunt.
There's nothing to be sorry about.
240:
All right. I'll try to be a little more
selfish from now on!
245:
Wait. What the hell?! We got
something incoming!
251:
Didn't... we run into something like
this on Paradise Isle?!
255:
Heh... Nothing screams there's
treasure nearby like a dragon
guarding the hoard!
258:
Couette, let's put our powers on
display!
269:
Time and space shall freeze before
me!
